{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.assetid: 5bad60aa-6084-4c7b-aefd-9b581f04382e\n---\n# Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures\nCounter name: Security Validation and Authentication Failures  \n  \n## Description  \n This counter is incremented whenever a message is rejected due to a security problem not covered by the \"Security Calls Not Authorized\" counter. Such problems include:  \n  \n-   Client token cannot be read from the message.  \n  \n-   Client token has failed authentication (bad password).  \n  \n-   Signature verification has failed (the message has been tampered).  \n  \n-   The message is a duplicate from a previous one, which can happen during a replay attack.  \n  \n-   A decryption failure has occurred.  \n  \n-   Some required elements (missing timestamp or encrypted data block) are missing from the message.  \n  \n-   Errors have occurred during TLSNEGO/SPNEGO handshake.\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,141],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.assetid: 5bad60aa-6084-4c7b-aefd-9b581f04382e","nodes":[{"content":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","nodes":[{"pos":[0,57],"content":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","nodes":[{"content":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","pos":[0,57]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[148,205],"content":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","linkify":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","nodes":[{"content":"Endpoint: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","pos":[0,57]}]},{"content":"Counter name: Security Validation and Authentication Failures","pos":[206,267]},{"pos":[276,287],"content":"Description","linkify":"Description","nodes":[{"content":"Description","pos":[0,11]}]},